snippet.textDisplay:
I am amazed by the background of this song.

This is from Tharparkar region where Sindhi people used to live before Pakistan was formed. (it was Sindh Region) 

Song is based on an women named Marvi, 

The King of Umarkot saw Marvi once in her village while passing by, and was amazed by her beauty. The king offered her to be a Queen by getting married with him, but she immediately rejected the offer as she was in love with a village guy named Khet who was a common farmer. 

King couldn't take the refusal, and to show his power he abducted Marvi.

Marvi was forced to stay in the palace. Kind tried to Lure her with his Wealth, gifted gold and many things, offered so many things to marry him, but she didn't accept anything.

She said "you cannot force Mehendi on my hand".

After many years, when King saw that Marvi is not changing her mind, so King gave and released her also gave permission to go back to her village Thar. 

Upon arriving at her village everyone was so surprised, nobody believed that she didn't let King touch her even though King was so Rich. So she had to prove her virginity. And when village women examined and agreed that she is Pure, those Women started Singing "Our Victor has arrived from her Prison her shyness is forsaken, You gave hope to dreams, The people of Thar is awakened now" (in Sindhi)

Thus this song was made to celebrate that Pride.
